==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subcutaneous
<hw>Sub`cu*ta"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Situated
under the skin; hypodermic.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sub`cu*ta"ne*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Subcutaneous operation</b></col> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>,
<cd>an operation performed without opening that part of the skin
opposite to, or over, the internal section.</cd></cs> <-- subcutaneous
injection, (Med) an injection method in which the injected liquid is
delivered directly under the skin, as contrasted with intramuscular or
intravenous injection. Also called subdermal injection. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subcuticular</ent>⟦br⟧
